The statement by NSC Spokesperson Ned Price acknowledges the one-year anniversary of the devastating earthquake in Nepal, which killed nearly 9,000 people and left millions without homes. The statement honors the victims and recognizes the efforts of those who risked their lives to save others, including six United States Marines who perished while providing relief. It also highlights the resilience and unity of the Nepali people in coming together to aid survivors and rebuild their country. The statement emphasizes that there is still much work to be done in rebuilding Nepal, and the United States Government and American people will continue to support and partner with Nepal to ensure a brighter and safer future for all Nepalis.